IMPORTANT — READ BEFORE DEPLOYMENT
================================================================

This repository (and any public snapshot thereof, including the
"BIZUSIZO" public repository at https://github.com/Bongekilenkosi/BIZUSIZO)
is released under the Apache License, Version 2.0 for purposes of
scientific reproducibility and independent verification of the
Bizusizo triage methodology.

It is NOT a deployment-ready toolkit.

Bizusizo as an operational clinical service is constituted by more
than the code in this repository. An operationally responsible
deployment requires, at minimum, all of the following — NONE of
which are included in or conferred by this repository:

  * Facility-specific configuration, including the operational
    DCSL keyword sets and threshold values used in production
    (maintained as separate governed configuration)
  * A live clinical governance loop with a named clinical
    governance lead, monthly audit cycles, and incident
    response pathways
  * Active integration with the South African primary healthcare
    referral pathway, ambulance dispatch, and CCMDD systems
  * POPIA compliance infrastructure including a current Data
    Protection Impact Assessment, audit logging, consent
    management, and a Data Processing Agreement with the
    deploying facility
  * Health Professions Council of South Africa (HPCSA) and
    Department of Health district-level approvals for the
    specific facilities at which deployment is intended
  * Production credentials for the messaging channel (Meta
    WhatsApp Cloud API) operated under identity-verified business
    accounts with facility-level consent flows
  * Native-speaker-validated keyword sets for all eleven official
    South African languages in which the system responds

Anyone who takes this code and deploys it to triage real patients
without establishing each of the above is operating a different
system, under different clinical and legal conditions, and under
their own liability. No warranty or clinical-safety assurance
is offered by the copyright holders in respect of such
deployments. See LICENSE for the warranty disclaimer terms.

